data_summary.description: Various Broadband and Health data have been combined in 2017
Number of residential (consumer) fixed connections over 200 Kbps in one direction per 100 households
% of the population living in census blocks with access to the most common download speed tier
% of the population living in census blocks with access to the most common upload speed tier
% of the population living in rural census blocks with access to fixed broadband service at 25/3 Mbps or higher
Unexpected outcomes of labor and delivery that result in significant short- or long-term consequences to a womans health
The number of deaths during pregnancy up to 42 days postpartum divided by the natality, multiplied by 100,000
